# I/O, Input, View & App

## Stdin protocol (do not change without explicit request)

1. Board rows until `Board:` marker (or legacy: rows then `Commands:`)
2. Commands: `click X Y`, `jump X Y`, `wait MS`, `print board`
3. Errors to stdout: `ERROR UNKNOWN_TOKEN`, `ERROR ROW_WIDTH_MISMATCH`, etc.
4. `main.cpp` wires `ScriptParser` + `BoardPrinter` into `ScriptRunner` and runs the whole protocol via
   `ScriptRunner::run(std::cin, std::cout)` — no hardcoded demo

## Layer roles

| Layer | Does | Does not |
|-------|------|----------|
| `io/` | Parse/print board text | Validate moves |
| `input/` | Map pixels/clicks → `Position` | Hold game state |
| `graphics/` | Load/scale sprites, play animations, read asset layout | Include OpenCV directly; hold game state |
| `view/` | `Img` wraps OpenCV; `Renderer` composites sprites + drives window | Mutate `Board` |
| `App` | Wire engine + I/O + input + view | Implement piece rules |

## Input flow

```
stdin → ScriptParser → ScriptRunner → Controller → GameEngine → snapshot → BoardPrinter
```

- `BoardMapper`: pixel `(x, y)` → grid `Position` using cell size constant; owned by the caller layer
  (e.g. `ScriptRunner`, UI loop), not by `Controller`
- `Controller`: operates strictly on `Position` (`click(const Position&)`, `jump(const Position&)`) and
  depends only on `GameEngine&`; the caller translates pixels via `BoardMapper::pixelToCell` first (an
  off-board result clears the selection for clicks and is ignored for jumps). Translate `click` into
  `requestMove(from, to)` based on selection state (clicking another same-color piece re-targets the
  selection instead of requesting a move); translate `jump` directly into `requestJump(at)`
- `ScriptParser`: parses the `Board:`/`Commands:` protocol into a `Board` + `ScriptCommand` list; implements
  the `IScriptSource` interface (command DTOs live in `texttests/ScriptCommand.h`)
- `ScriptRunner`: replays parsed commands against a fresh `GameEngine`/`Controller`, writing `print board`
  output; receives its `IScriptSource` and `IBoardPrinter` collaborators by const reference through its
  constructor (dependency injection). `main.cpp` is the composition root: it constructs the concrete
  `ScriptParser`/`BoardPrinter`, wires them into `ScriptRunner`, then calls `run(std::cin, std::cout)`

## View flow

- Receive `GameSnapshot` const reference or value copy
- No direct `Board` access; all display data comes from the snapshot DTO
- Keep rendering logic free of rule checks

## Graphics flow (interactive animated board)

```
board.csv → graphics::BoardLayout → GraphicsApplication
          → AnimationCache → PieceVisual (map of state → Animation)
          → Renderer.showFrame(PlacedSprite[]) → window
```

- `BoardLayoutLoader` reads the asset layout once
- `AnimationCache::get` reads `config.json` once per (piece, state, size) and caches an `AnimationSpec`
- `PieceVisual` holds `map<string, Animation>` for states (`idle`, `move`, `jump`, `short_rest`,
  `long_rest`); missing states fall back to `idle` via `animationFor`
- `GraphicsApplication` owns the frame loop (delta time, `engine.wait`, click handling, sprite build)
- Resting pieces play `short_rest` / `long_rest` from `engine.activeRests()`; cooldown overlays are
  yellow (long) / blue (short) cell fills that shrink with `RestView::remaining`
- `Renderer` depends on `Img` only: clones the board background, draws `CellOverlay`s then each
  `PlacedSprite`, displays one window. The loop exits on ESC/Q **or** `Renderer::isOpen()` == false
- `graphics_main.cpp` is a thin entry point (`build.bat graphics`) that loads assets and calls
  `GraphicsApplication::run()`

## Exception handling

### I/O (`io/`)

- Expected parse failures → `BoardParseStatus` + stdout codes (`ERROR UNKNOWN_TOKEN`, etc.) — not exceptions
- Throw `std::runtime_error` only for broken streams; let `ScriptRunner` catch
- `BoardPrinter`: throw on bad stream; no try-catch wrapper

### Input (`input/`)

- `BoardMapper::pixelToCell`: return `std::nullopt` for off-board pixels — no exceptions for normal input
- `BoardMapper` constructor: throw on invalid dimensions
- `Controller::click` / `jump`: catch unexpected errors → status DTO with `runtime_error`; clear selection on failure

### View (`view/`)

- `Img`: Qama Tech course wrapper — the **only** place OpenCV is allowed (`Img.h` / `Img.cpp`); validate and throw (missing file, bad draw rect) — no try-catch; `graphics_main` is the top catcher for the graphics app
- All other view/graphics code uses the `Img` API only — no direct OpenCV includes

### Text tests & app

- `ScriptParser`: throw on malformed command syntax or unreadable stream; propagate to `ScriptRunner`
- `ScriptRunner::run`: **the** recovery boundary for the stdin app — single catch, log to `stderr`, `ERROR RUNTIME_FAILURE` to stdout
- `main`: outer safety net — catch, log, exit non-zero
